# Architecture Patterns

## Module Structure

Every module under `src/modules/{module}/` has exactly four files:

```
{module}.routes.ts      → route definitions + middleware chain only
{module}.controller.ts  → parse req → call one service method → send response
{module}.service.ts     → business logic + DB/cache/queue calls
{module}.schemas.ts     → Zod schemas + inferred types + response interfaces
```

**Modules:** `auth`, `users`, `tickets`, `comments`, `attachments`

Shared logic → `src/utils/`; cross-cutting middleware → `src/middlewares/`

## Middleware Stack Order (fixed — never reorder)

`helmet` → `cors` → `compression` → `morgan` → `express.json` → `express.urlencoded` → `cookieParser` → `passport.initialize` → `authLimiter` (`/api/v1/auth/*`) → routes → `errorHandler` (last)

## Route File Pattern

```ts
router.get('/', authenticate, validateQuery(listSchema), controller.list);
router.post('/', authenticate, validateBody(createSchema), controller.create);
router.post('/:id/assign', authenticate, requireRole('ADMIN'), validateBody(assignSchema), controller.assign);
```

`authenticate` + `requireRole` + `validateBody`/`validateQuery` are route-level middleware — never inside controllers.

## API Design

- **Base URL:** `/api/v1/{resource}` — plural nouns, kebab-case, no verbs
- **Health check:** `GET /health` (outside versioned prefix)
- **Nested resources:** `GET /api/v1/tickets/:id/comments`
- Never modify `v1` endpoints in a breaking way — add `v2` mounted alongside

| Operation | Method | Success Code |
|---|---|---|
| List | `GET /` | 200 |
| Get single | `GET /:id` | 200 / 404 |
| Create | `POST /` | 201 |
| Full replace | `PUT /:id` | 200 |
| Partial update | `PATCH /:id` | 200 |
| Delete | `DELETE /:id` | 204 (no body) |

## Query Filters (list endpoints)

`?status=OPEN&priority=HIGH&assignedTo=<uuid>&page=1&limit=20&sortBy=createdAt&order=desc`

- Keys `camelCase`; ENUM values uppercase to match DB
- `page` 1-based; `limit` default 20, max 100

## Jobs & Storage (when implemented)

```
src/jobs/
  queues.ts / emailWorker.ts / autoCloseWorker.ts / mailer.ts

src/storage/
  index.ts (IStorageBackend + factory) / local.ts / s3.ts
```

Queue adds happen in **services** after a successful DB write — never in controllers.
Always wrap queue `.add()` in try/catch; log failure but never re-throw (fire-and-forget).

## Directory Map

```
bin/www.ts                  server bootstrap + graceful shutdown
src/
  app.ts                    middleware stack + route mounting
  config/index.ts           typed Config — only place process.env is read
  config/postgres.ts        pg.Pool singleton
  config/redis.ts           ioredis singleton
  db/schema.sql             idempotent DDL — source of truth
  db/migrate.ts             migration runner
  db/admin-seed.ts          seed script
  middlewares/errorHandler.ts  global 4-arg handler (last in app.ts)
  modules/                  feature modules
  utils/response.ts         success() / error()
dist/                       compiled JS output (never edit)
```
